obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29999)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=29999&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Muslim Women (Protection of Rights on`
  line `Divorce) Act, 1986.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30000)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30000&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "divorced woman" means a Muslim woman who was married according to Muslim law, and`
  line `has been divorced by, or has obtained divorce from, her husband in accordance with Muslim law;`
  line
  line `(b) "iddat period" means, in the case of a divorced woman,`
  line
  line `(i) three menstrual courses after the date of divorce, if she is subject to menstruation;`
  line
  line `(ii) three lunar months after her divorce, if she is not subject to menstruation; and`
  line
  line `(iii) if she is enceinte at the time of her divorce, the period between the divorce and the`
  line `delivery of her child or the termination of her pregnancy, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(c) "Magistrate" means a Magistrate of the First class exercising jurisdiction under the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) in the area where the divorced woman resides;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30001)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Mahr or other properties of Muslim woman to be given to her at the time of divorce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30001&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, a divorced woman shall`
  line `be entitled to`
  line
  line `(a) a reasonable and fair provision and maintenance to be made and paid to her within the idda`
  line `tperiod by her former husband;`
  line
  line `(b) where she herself maintains the children born to her before or after her divorce, a reasonable`
  line `and fair provision and maintenance to be made and paid by her former husband for a period of two`
  line `years from the respective dates of birth of such children;`
  line
  line `(c) an amount equal to the sum of mahr or dower agreed to be paid to her at the time of her`
  line `marriage or at any time thereafter according to Muslim law; and`
  line
  line `(d) all the properties given to her before or at the time of marriage or after her marriage by her`
  line `relatives or friends or the husband or any relatives of the husband or his friends.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a reasonable and fair provision and maintenance or the amount of mahr or dower due has`
  line `not been made or paid or the properties referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) have not been delivered`
  line `to a divorced woman on her divorce, she or any one duly authorised by her may, on her behalf, make an`
  line `application to a Magistrate for an order for payment of such provision and maintenance, mahr or dower or`
  line `the delivery of properties, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application has been made under sub-section (2) by a divorced woman, the Magistrate`
  line `may, if he is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) her husband having sufficient means, has failed or neglected to make or pay her within the`
  line `iddat period a reasonable and fair provision and maintenance for her and the children; or`
  line
  line `(b) the amount equal to the sum of mahr or dower has not been paid or that the properties referred`
  line `to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) have not been delivered to her,`
  line
  line `make an order, within one month of the date of the filing of the application, directing her former husband`
  line `to pay such reasonable and fair provision and maintenance to the divorced woman as he may determine as`
  line `it and proper having regard to the needs of the divorced woman, the standard of life enjoyed by her during`
  line `her marriage and the means of her former husband or, as the case may be, for the payment of such mahr`
  line `or dower or the delivery of such properties referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) the divorced`
  line `woman:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate finds it impracticable to dispose of the application within the said`
  line `period, he may, for reasons to be recorded by him, dispose of the application after the said period.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person against whom an order has been made under sub-section (3) fails without sufficient`
  line `cause to comply with the order, the Magistrate may issue a warrant for levying the amount of`
  line `maintenance or mahr or dower due in the manner provided for levying fines under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), and may sentence such person, for the whole or part of any amount`
  line `remaining unpaid after the execution of the warrant, to imprisonment for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year or until payment if sooner made, subject to such person being heard in defence and the said sentence`
  line `being imposed according to the provisions of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30002)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Order for payment of maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30002&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, where a Magistrate is satisfied that a`
  line `divorced woman has not re-married and is not able to maintain herself after the iddat period, he may`
  line `make an order directing such of her relatives as would be entitled to inherit her property on her death`
  line `according to Muslim law to pay such reasonable and fair maintenance to her as he may determine fit and`
  line `proper, having regard to the needs of the divorced woman, the standard of life enjoyed by her during her`
  line `marriage and the means of such relatives and such maintenance shall be payable by such relatives in the`
  line `proportions in which they would inherit he property and at such periods as he may specify in his order:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such divorced woman has children, the Magistrate shall order only such children`
  line `to pay maintenance to her, and in the event of any such children being unable to pay such maintenance,`
  line `the Magistrate shall order the parents of such divorced woman to pay maintenance to her:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if any of the parents is unable to pay his or her share of the maintenance ordered`
  line `by the Magistrate on the ground of his or her not having the means to pay the same, the Magistrate may,`
  line `on proof of such inability being furnished to him, order that the share of such relatives in the maintenance`
  line `ordered by him be paid by such of the other relatives as may appear to the Magistrate to have the means`
  line `of paying the same in such proportions as the Magistrate may think fit to order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a divorced woman is unable to maintain herself and she has no relatives as mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) or such relatives or any one of them have not enough means to pay the maintenance`
  line `ordered by the Magistrate or the other relatives have not the means to pay the shares of those relatives`
  line `whose shares have been ordered by the Magistrate to be paid by such other relatives under the second`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1), the Magistrate may, by order, direct the State Wakf Board established under`
  line `section 9 of the Wakf Act, 1954 (29 of 1954), or under any other law for the time being in force in a State,`
  line `functioning in the area in which the woman resides, to pay such maintenance as determined by him under`
  line `sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, to pay the shares of such of the relatives who are unable to pay, at`
  line `such periods as he may specify in his order.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30003)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Option to be governed by the provisions of sections 125 to 128 of Act 2 of 1974.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30003&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If on the date`
  line `of the first hearing of the application under sub-section (2) of section 3, a divorced woman and her former`
  line `husband declare, by affidavit or any other declaration in writing in such form as may be prescribed, either`
  line `jointly or separately, that they would prefer to be governed by the provisions of sections 125 to 128 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), and file such affidavit or declaration in the court hearing`
  line `the application, the Magistrate shall dispose of such application accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "date of the first hearing of the application" means the`
  line `date fixed in the summons for the attendance of the respondent to the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30004)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30004&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of the affidavit or other declaration in writing to be filed under section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Magistrate in disposing of applications under this Act,`
  line `including the serving of notices to the parties to such applications, dates of hearing of such`
  line `applications and other matters;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30005)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331&sectionId=30005&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00034_198625_1517807327331
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every application by a divorced woman under section 125 or under`
  line `section 127 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) pending before a Magistrate on the`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall, notwithstanding anything contained in that Code and subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 5 of this Act, be disposed of by such Magistrate in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
